<item>
            <title>[NET-74] [net]Telnet option handlers subnegotiations does not handle 0xFF correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-74</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in accordance to RFC855: &quot;Finally, if parameters in an option &quot;subnegotiation&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
include a byte with a value of 255, it is necessary to double this byte in&lt;br/&gt;
accordance the general TELNET rules.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve actually encontered this while implementing WindowSize option handler, but&lt;br/&gt;
it seems that all the currently avilable handlers are vulnerable to this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
