                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12887241" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2010 22:15:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks as though TelnetInputStream does handle IAC+IAC correctly when processing options, so it is just when generating options that the problem may arise.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12887247" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2010 23:03:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that the individual handlers have to deal with doubling any 255 bytes themselves - TelnetClient only adds the IAC SB / IAC SE wrapper.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only the WindowSize option handler can generate the byte 255, and it already takes this into account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added a test case for the code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
